Invocation Name: museum of the gulf coast radio
des: Museum of the Gulf Coast Radio captures the music and spirit of the lively Gulf Coast music scene of yesterday and today. The Gulf of Mexico coastal region that stretches from Southeast Texas to New Orleans is the birthplace of many unique genres of music including jazz, rhythm & blues, rock, soul, country, swamp pop, and Cajun/zydeco music. This web-based radio station plays a mix of the music that made our part of the world famous and features selected rock, swamp pop and soul classics from the 1950's to the 1980's. In addition, our programing provides interviews, background, perspective, and insight into the rich and vibrant musical heritage that is uniquely American and uniquely Gulf Coast.
